[{"id":"VR106125","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR106068.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A researcher claims that an individual has protoporphyria, based on a physical exam. Which of the following techniques would most likely confirm the researcher’s claim?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR106125_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a pedigree of the incidence of protoporphyria in four generations of a particular family. An affected male and an unaffected female represent the first generation. They produce six second-generation children, including four affected females and two unaffected males. One of the unaffected second-generation males has children with an affected female. They produce five third-generation children, including an affected male, an affected female, two unaffected males, and an unaffected female. The affected third-generation male has children with an unaffected female. They produce four fourth-generation children, including three affected females and an unaffected male. One of the affected second-generation females has children with an affected male. They produce four third-generation children, including two unaffected males and two affected females.\" height=\"160\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR106068.g01.png\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"standalone_statement style:1\">Figure 1. Incidence of protoporphyria in a particular family</p>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\">Protoporphyria is a genetic disorder characterized by an extreme sensitivity to sunlight. One form of protoporphyria is caused by a mutation in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A L A S 2\"><math alttext=\"A L A S 2\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>L</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>S</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></mrow></math></span></span> gene that results in the accumulation of protoporphyrin, an organic compound, in the blood, liver, and skin. The pedigree in Figure 1 shows the incidence of protoporphyria in a particular family.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Transforming bacteria with the mutant variation of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A L A S 2\"><math alttext=\"A L A S 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>L</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>S</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to measure gene expression</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Culturing cells from the individual in the lab and measuring the cells’ growth rate</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Using light microscopy to examine the individual’s chromosomes during metaphase</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Determining the nucleotide sequence of the individual’s <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A L A S 2\"><math alttext=\"A L A S 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>L</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>S</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> alleles</p>"],"answer":3}]